observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the:

33. Sangguniang Bayan Secretary transmit to the Sangguniang Panlalawigan for review and approval all appropriation;

34. Members of the Sangguniang Bayan require the submission of the Supplemental Annual Investment Plans and Certification of Funding Source before enacting proposed appropriation ordinances on the realignment of funds;

35. Members of the Local Development Council to prepare a supplemental Annual Investment Program to support the changes in the annual budget; and

36. OIC-Municipal Budget Officer and OIC-Municipal Accountant process payment for the utilization of realigned funds only for programs, activities and projects which are included in the supplemental Annual Investment Plan to ensure legality of the transactions.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant:

Spearhead the immediate liquidation of the cash advances granted to LGU officials/employees. 
Introduce controls that would assure that cash advances are liquidated or reported as soon as the purpose of the cash advance is served;
Refrain from granting additional cash advances to officers and employees with unsettled cash advances to avoid the accumulation of unliquidated cash advances; 
Request write-off of long outstanding/dormant cash advances and attached therein complete documents as enumerated in COA Circular 2016-005;
Cause the withholding of salaries or any money due the officers and employees with overdue unliquidated cash advances to compel its settlement; and
File appropriate charges against persons liable if warranted, for continuous failure to settle their accountabilities upon demand.
